        <num>CC 2670</num>
        <heading>2670.  Contract to lease</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2670.  Contract to lease
A contract to enter into a lease at a future time is enforceable by either party if there was agreement as to the thing to be leased and the rent, unless the parties understood that the contract would not be binding until reduced to writing or until its other terms were agreed upon.</p>
        </content>
